My Meme

The meme I have created is a rendition of the Fancy Pooh meme. Essentially, whatever is in the same row as the normal Pooh, is seen as the standard version; whereas, the lower row contains a classier/superior version of the above idea. Hence, it is superior to make memes with RStudios as opposed to with Photoshop.

library(magick)
library(tidyverse)
library(magick)

# First, load in images of both fancy/normal Pooh
fancy_pooh <- image_read("https://images-wixmp-ed30a86b8c4ca887773594c2.wixmp.com/i/36e14bc4-9a1e-4033-9878-8f1981f48eed/dd7rr4c-9a080e4e-e2a3-44ef-8bff-8cc7241a41c0.png/v1/fill/w_602,h_378,q_80,strp/fancy_pooh_by_shadow_of_devotion_dd7rr4c-fullview.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(200)%>% 
  image_crop("0x105")

normal_pooh <- image_read("https://uploads.dailydot.com/2019/04/winnie-the-pooh.jpg?auto=compress&fm=pjpg") %>% 
  image_scale(200)

# Second, create text with relative positioning 
fancy_text <- image_blank(width = 200, 
                          height = 100, 
                          color = "#FFFFFF") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Making Memes \nWith RStudio",
                 color = "#000000",
                 size = 20,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

normal_text <- image_blank(width = 200, 
                          height = 100, 
                          color = "#FFFFFF") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Making Memes \nWith Photoshop",
                 color = "#000000",
                 size = 20,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

# Third, Append each image with texts
row2 <- c(fancy_pooh,fancy_text) %>% image_append()
row1 <- c(normal_pooh,normal_text) %>% image_append()

# Fourth, Append both rows together
meme <- c(row1, row2) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)
meme
# Fifth, write image to png
image_write(meme, "my_meme.png")

My Animated GIF

For the GIF I knew finding sequential photos was extremely difficult, thus I decided to focus on a trippy art theme. This would create a more streamlined GIF which wasnt just a collation of random frames.

library(magick)

# First, load all images and rescale them
visual1 <- image_read("https://static.vecteezy.com/system/resources/thumbnails/009/636/392/original/motion-background-psychedelic-kaleidoscope-patterns-kaleidoscope-sequence-patterns-kaleidoscopic-patterns-bubbling-geometric-shapes-vj-loop-neon-kaleidoscope-looping-animation-free-video.jpg") %>%
  image_scale("550")

visual2 <- image_read("https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2022/07/15/07/34/psychedelic-7322589_1280.jpg") %>%
  image_scale("550")

visual3 <- image_read("https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcTLVpzXfWbvpdKu0S2VaPI3AEgS-yWfDCYVM3CLWYv-5Y8xN3uZrOHVjfJQJjjguxA6BQA&usqp=CAU") %>%
  image_scale("550")

visual4 <- image_read("https://static.vecteezy.com/system/resources/thumbnails/009/295/675/small_2x/motion-background-psychedelic-kaleidoscope-patterns-kaleidoscope-sequence-patterns-kaleidoscopic-patterns-bubbling-geometric-shapes-vj-loop-neon-kaleidoscope-looping-animation-free-video.jpg") %>%
  image_scale("550")

visual5 <- image_read("https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcTiAHxrbV_sT8b7VDdYgQfQku6xCP1FMykb2BLAR7YDzVx4FxWVGhI4qCpt9WdGvMn5oy4&usqp=CAU") %>%
  image_scale("550")

visual6 <- image_read("https://static.vecteezy.com/system/resources/thumbnails/009/295/674/original/motion-background-psychedelic-kaleidoscope-patterns-kaleidoscope-sequence-patterns-kaleidoscopic-patterns-bubbling-geometric-shapes-vj-loop-neon-kaleidoscope-looping-animation-free-video.jpg") %>%
  image_scale("550")

# Second, create the vector of frames
frames <- c(visual2, 
            visual1, 
            visual2, 
            visual3, 
            visual2, 
            visual4, 
            visual2, 
            visual5, 
            visual2, 
            visual6)

# Third, animate the frames
trip_gif <- image_animate(frames)

# Fourth, save animation as gif
trip_gif %>% image_write("my_animation.gif")
